<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A body has been found in the search for a missing teenager from Bury.</p>

<p>Matthew Young, 17, was last seen on Broad Street, in Bury town centre, at around 2.30pm on Wednesday.</p>

<p>Police said he failed to return home after attending college for the day and described it as being ‘out of character’.</p>

<p>Matthew Young, 17, (pictured) was last seen on Broad Street, in Bury town centre, at around 2.30pm on Wednesday</p>

<p>A public appeal for help was issued earlier today as concerns grew for the teenager.</p>

<p>Officers searching for Matthew announced that they found a body last night.</p>

<p>Formal identification has not yet taken place.</p>

<p>Police say they are not treating the death as suspicious.</p>

<p>Matthew was described as a white, 6ft tall male, of slim build with ginger hair and glasses.</p>

<p>He was last seen wearing a green jacket, dark jeans, black boots and was carrying a black rucksack.</p>
